The White House has issued a statement condemning the terrorist attack in Dhaka, Bangladesh that occurred on July 1-2. The United States is in contact with Bangladeshi authorities and has offered assistance. The attack resulted in approximately 20 deaths, including an American citizen, Bangladeshi law enforcement personnel, and citizens of other nations. The statement expresses condolences to the families and hopes for a quick recovery for the injured. The United States is committed to standing with Bangladesh and the international community in the fight against terrorism.